imperialism, and cultural essentialism by feminists from the global South; and the sex-positive positions of many feminists involved in debates about sex work and pornography. The Grip of Sexual Violence in Conflict offers a detailed examination of how these feminist commitments were not merely deprioritized, but undermined, by efforts to address the issue of sexual violence in conflict. Engle's analysis reinvigorates vital debates about feminist goals and priorities, and spurs readers to question much of today's common sense about the causes, effects, and proper responses to sexual violence in conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aFeminist jurisprudence. 0aRape as a weapon of war. 7aLAW / Civil Rights.2bisacsh  aarmed conflict.  aethnic conflict.  afeminism.  ainternational criminal law.  ainternational human rights.  apeace.  arape.  asexual violence.  awar.  awomen’s human rights.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishz978311070486008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020z9783110704587oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361125240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503611252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503611252.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070486-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020